Description: Nu Kitchens can help you with your new or existing kitchen from start to finish.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Nu Kitchens was established in 1977 to provide local homeowners and builders with a source for quality kitchen cabinets. From it's humble beginnings in Pat and Ila Dillon's kitchen and garage in front of the current business, Nu Kitchens has grown. During the first 6 months of business they sold 4 semi loads of cabinets that were manufactured by Del Mar Cabinets in Union City, Indiana. Andy Anderson was hired in 1977 as a salesman. His responsibilities grew from doing sales to include drawing up plans, unloading trucks and delivery. He was with Nu Kitchens for 30 years and instrumental in helping grow the business. Nu Kitchens moved into the building that houses the current showroom and it has undergone 2 expansions and the construction of a warehouse. In 1999 Pat purchased the old lumber yard in Stockwell and began Nu Counters. Pat passed on in 2000. Nu Counters was established to compliment Nu Kitchens and fill the needs of the community. Nu Counters outgrew the old building and built a new facility in 2006. Nu Kitchens now consists of a 3000 square foot showroom and a 6000 square foot warehouse at the south side facility. Nu Counters is a 2500 square foot production operation in Stockwell, Indiana, just minutes from Nu Kitchens.

Full Description: Since 1998, SalesOutlook, Inc. has pioneered the use of MS-Outlook and Exchange Server as the technology platform for a complete CRM System. SalesOutlook is a very cost effective CRM Solution because it is simple to install, easy to use and fully customizable. SalesOutlook is a unique and comprehensive CRM & Email Marketing System that was developed from the ground up to be fully embedded into the folder structure of Microsoft Outlook. This system is the first of its kind, and was designed to combine the functionality of a CRM system with the user-friendly aspects and familiarity of Microsoft Outlook. SalesOutlook CRM can be implemented within minutes and automatically syncs all customer data with MS Exchange.  All files and email correspondence are saved to the contact's profile, and because the SalesOutlook Database resides in the folder structure of MS-Outlook, there is no need for an external MS-SQL server database.  Reaching contacts with Broadcast Email Campaigns is greatly simplified with the integration of SalesOutlook CRM and Constant Contact.  These Broadcast Email Campaigns are available in HTML or RTF formats, offering users more flexiblility when it comes to sending custom email blasts to a client base. This seamless integration to Constant Contact, means that SalesOutlook CRM can efficiently and quickly create the ideal email campaign for your targeted contacts. Each member of your team is able to view the history for each contact. SalesOutlook CRM's intuitive interface provides a host of features that optimize the user experience. Contacts can be dragged and dropped into different lead categories, such as “Opportunity” or “Customer Inquiry” directly from the email interface. By right-clicking on a customer name, users can easily access contact information, providing instant visibility into all the necessary information related to any particular buyer. SalesOutlook CRM is a specialized system that builds upon a frequently-used email medium to create a CRM that will optimize user efficiency and boost customer satisfaction. It's a great fit for growing companies in a variety of vertical industries.
